data.title: Discovery Labels for Kids
data.text: Benjamin Franklin was born on January 17, 1706 in Boston, Massachusetts, the tenth son of Josiah and Abiah Franklin. Josiah, a tallow candle and soap maker emigrated from England in 1683 to improve his finances and practice his Puritan faith. Abiah was the daughter of Peter Folger, a schoolmaster and surveyor in Nantucket.
